This is WHY this Fashion Show was so important to me! 🙏❤️#nyfw @pamelaquinzi 

On December 2022, during my trip to New York after few days, all of a sudden I felt very sick, I had to run to the Emergency Room and after discovering what it was going on I had to immediately take the first flight to Rome, Italy and go straight to the Hospital.
.
It’s been more than a month of Doctors appointments, medications and at the end, the day of my birthday 02.02 I got surgery. They removed my gallbladder full of small stones very dangerous with an emergency surgery. This is why the day of my birthday I felt REBORN. I feel blessed.

I want to thank my Doctor in Italy 🇮🇹 and all the incredible people I met during this journey, all the nurses and everyone that works to help people in this world. 

During this weeks I knew that my recovery wasn’t going to be fast, I really need to take it slow, so i knew I couldn’t make it to be there for NYFW, but one thing I knew…I had you guys!
@tashadwhaj and Herbert Fox helped me to put together an amazing event last night, and WE DID IT!

I shipped my New Kilame Collection to Tasha, we organized the models and outfits and we made…MAGIC! Pure New York Magic!

I was home, on video calls and it was incredible to see all of you there, photographers, friends, you are family to me! The Empire State Building was shining for us! The Bowery rooftop was the perfect frame to this unbelievable moment.

Thank you @oddmodcreations for being part of this event and this beautiful moment of life and love. Congratulations on your debut as a Jewelry Designer.

Soon I will see everyone again in New York ❤️ Now is time to recover, cheers to life and friendship.

Thank you,
Forever your @cinderellaofnewyork 
.
.
.

A little bit of my medical adventure around the world…🚑🏥 @pamelaquinzi 
.
This is how I spent the day of my birthday this year! Got surgery exactly on February 2nd in Italy. 😅🥳🫶🏻
I didn’t eat any chocolate but it was a cute gift from my mom at 6am before going to the Hospital. The first day I was in so much pain, couldn’t eat anything. The second day I was able to eat something. The food at the Hospital wasn’t really bad, at the end still was ITALIAN FOOD 🇮🇹Lol In New York a dish like this with fish could cost $50🤣 Looking at the bright side of the story Hahahah 
.
If you keep scrolling, you will see few videos of me when I first got sick at the Emergency Room in New York in December. I was in an insane pain and so freaking out, till they gave me very strong pain killers and I took the first plane ✈️ to go back to Italy.
.
After more than a month of medications, doctors appointments (where I got different opinions on my situation) I finally got surgery in the Hospital in Viterbo near Rome. Thank you to Doctor M. that seriously saved me and removed my gallbladder full of freaking stones so dangerous. I’ll never be thankful enough. The pain was real. 
.
Now is time to recover, heal, breath. 
Feeling blessed, strong and loved.
Thank you. 💕
@cinderellaofnewyork 
.
Funny is how in few of this days I was wearing my same sweater @kilame New York Fashion Week…probably was a sign, that guided me till the end of this adventure for then being able (from remote) to organize my Fashion Show! Life is amazing 🙏❤️
.
.
